    <worksheet name='Summerize'>
      <layout-options>
        <title>
          <formatted-text>
            <run bold='true'>Summerize
1.The most Important factor - Experience</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000'>Years of experience show the strongest positive relationship with salary.</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000'>
As experience increases, salary tends to rise significantly across all roles.</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000'>2. Second Factor - Certifications
Certifications demonstrate a moderate positive impact on salary.</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000'>
While the trend is not steep, certified individuals generally earn more than those with fewer or no certifications.</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000'>3. Least Impact - Number of Skills</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000'>The number of skills shows a weak correlation with salary.</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000'>
Having more skills does not necessarily translate to higher pay, suggesting that skill relevance and specialization matter more than quantity. </run>
          </formatted-text>
        </title>
      </layout-options>
      <table>
        <view>
          <datasources />
          <aggregation value='true' />
